Class Command

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.ncsu.csc216.tracker.requirement.Command
  • public class Command
extends java.lang.Object
    Objected used by the GUI to help the requirement object transition through states using the command enums. By encapsulating the requirement object, the enum can be used for permisisons through different states

    • Constructor Detail

      • Command

        public Command​(CommandValue designation,
               java.lang.String summary,
               java.lang.String acceptanceTestId,
               int priority,
               java.lang.String estimate,
               java.lang.String developerId,
               Rejection resolutionReason)
        Constructs a Command object that will encapsulate a Requirement. This command will be used by the finite state machine to determine what values to change at what state the requirement is currently at.
        Parameters:
        designation - The command enum
        summary - the requirements summary
        acceptanceTestId - the requirements acceptanceTestId
        priority - the requirements priority
        estimate - the requirements estimate
        developerId - the requirements developerId
        resolutionReason - the requirements resolutionReason
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if during the ACCEPT command, estimate is a null or empty string and priority is not between 1 and 3
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if during the REJECT command and the resolutionReason is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if during the ASSIGN command and the developerId is either empty or null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if during the REVISE command, either the summary or acceptanceTestId are a null or empty string
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if designation is null
